In terminal after having installed GIT

git config --global user.email guillaume.honore@gmail.com

git config --list


On the laptop, create a repository.
Terminal, go to this rep. Type:
$ git init
This will initialise this rep as a git rep.

$ git status
This will show the different files and if there is a conflict (file not commited for instance)

$ git add . 
Will add all the files to the git rep.

$ git commit -m "first commit" 
-m is message. 

$ git log --oneline
Shows comments on all the previous commit

$ git checkout REFERENCE_OBTAINED_WITH_ABOVE_COMMAND file
Example
$ git checkoutc1213e8 Templates/new.html
This will revert this file to the previous committed version!

